# askdev: Android Error CLI Assistant

askdev is a Python-based CLI tool that helps Android developers debug crash logs and exceptions directly from their terminal. It matches errors against a local database and (optionally) uses AI for suggestions.

## Features
- Explain Android errors from log files or direct input
- Suggest fixes using a local error database
- Optional `--ai` flag for LLM-based suggestions (OpenRouter/Ollama integration planned)
- Beautiful output with Rich

## Installation

```sh
pipx install .
```

## Usage

```sh
# Analyze log file
askdev logcat.txt
askdev crash_log.txt

# Use AI suggestions
askdev logcat.txt --ai

# Direct text input
askdev --text "java.lang.NullPointerException: Attempt to invoke virtual method"

# Read from stdin
cat logcat.txt | askdev --stdin
adb logcat | askdev --stdin

# Get help
askdev --help
```

